2900. FROM CHRISTOPHER GERING.

Leipzig MS. Augsburg. EE. 200. 30 January 1534.

[An original letter. autograph throughout. The date seems to receive con- firmation from Ep. 2906. 1 18-24. carried back. it is to be inferred. by the bearet of the present letter; where a letter to Paungartner is mentioned, not extant, presumably thanking him for his gift, and where it is taken as likely that Paungartner is not in Augsburg (in which case Erasmus' letter to him is to be hancled to Gering). On 26 June 1534 (EE2. 118 = Ep. 2949) and 28 Jan. 1535 (EE. 216 = Ep. 2089) Gering wrote to Erasmus other lettera equally brief and business-like. In Ep. 2906. 124 Erasmus calls him Paungartner's famulus (here minister). In Ep. 2989 he signs himself ‘secretarius’. In Basle MS. G. II. 17. 287-00 are letters of 1537 to Boniface Amerbach from Gering‚ about books sent to his master John Paungartner, including the Colloquia Erasmi. But otherwise we know nothing of him.]
